Install a fresh copy of Ubuntu

Update distribution
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade

Remove and purge ubuntu video drivers

Install NVIDIA drivers
sudo apt-get install nvidia-current
sudo apt-get install nvidia-current-update

Install CUDA and CUDA Toolkit (standard procedure)

Include /usr/local/cuda/bin in path
Set LD_LIBRARY_PATH /usr/local/cuda/lib64

Install Apache2

Install ANACONDA (It is recommended, you may opt for individual installation of packages)
Using:
http://uoa-eresearch.github.io/eresearch-cookbook/recipe/2014/11/20/conda/
Create a virtual environment using conda command inside anaconda2/envs
conda create -n image_search python=x.x anaconda
Activate venv image_search
source activate image_search

Install Django and mod_wsgi (Google for instructions)

Create an entry for VirtualHost wonders.pc.hiit.fi in /etc/hosts
Create a file wonders.pc.hiit.fi.conf inside /etc/apache2/sites-available

Enable the virtual host by
sudo a2ensite wonders.pc.hiit.fi
(Remember do not use .conf extension in this command, this command basically makes a symlink of this file inside /etc/apache2/sites-enabled)

Create a file Imse.wsgi inside conf directory under /ldata/Imse
